SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: EL CAJON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Cajon police arrested a Spring Valley man Wednesday night after he allegedly 
held a group of store clerks hostage at knifepoint during a robbery attempt. 
</P>
<P>
Police arrested Migel Angel Marrugo, 32, outside Leo's Market Wednesday about 9 
p.m., police dispatcher Patti Conrad said. 
</P>
<P>
A passer-by alerted police after spotting the robbery going on at the market, 
which is in the 600 block of El Cajon Boulevard, Conrad said. 
</P>
<P>
After police surrounded the building, Marrugo allegedly held the store 
employees briefly as hostages, then fled out the store's back door alone. 
</P>
<P>
Two officers arrested Marrugo outside after a short scuffle, Conrad said. No 
injuries were reported. 
</P>
