<TEXT>
<P>
Police are investigating the death of a Southeast San Diego man whose body was 
found near his front doorstep Thursday morning. 
</P>
<P>
Officers responding to a call at 7 a.m. Thursday in the 5300 block of Geneva 
Avenue found the body of Francisco Domingo Estrada, 27, just a few feet from 
the front doorstep of his home, police spokesman Bill Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
