<HEADLINE>
<P>
HULDAH C. BOUGHTON; HOMEMAKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Huldah C. Boughton, a homemaker and longtime Van Nuys resident, has died in 
Camarillo. She was 94. 
</P>
<P>
Born Huldah Katherine in Newark, N.J., she died Wednesday of congestive heart 
failure, said her daughter, Huldah Sampson. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Boughton was married in 1915 to her husband of 63 years, Percy Boughton, 
who died in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
The couple moved from New Jersey to California in 1951 to live close to their 
daughter and grandchildren in Van Nuys. She moved to Camarillo early this year. 
</P>
<P>
She is survived by her daughter, who lives in Camarillo; grandsons Rod Black of 
Rio Vista, Calif., and Drew Black of Simi Valley, and six great-grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial service will be held Saturday at Boughton's Camarillo home with the 
immediate family only. Arrangements were made by Pierce Bros. Griffin Mortuary 
in Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
Donations can be made in Mrs. Boughton's name to the American Heart Assn. or to 
charities for the blind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
