<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAMILY OUT FOR WALK FINDS MAN'S BODY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man in his early 20s was found dead in Sunland on Thursday afternoon, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The body of the man, whose name was not being released pending notification of 
his relatives, was found about 1 p.m. by a woman walking with her children in 
the hills off La Tuna Canyon Road a mile south of the Simi Valley Freeway, Los 
Angeles Police Sgt. Sol Polen said. 
</P>
<P>
The man died of multiple gunshot wounds, Polen said. No suspects are in custody 
and no motive has been established, Polen said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
