<HEADLINE>
<P>
FULL WEEKEND OF AUTO RACES SCHEDULED FOR VENTURA COUNTY FAIRGROUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The first Ventura County Fair Motorsports Weekend, taking place tonight through 
Sunday at the fairgrounds race track, will offer competition in seven classes 
of vehicles and four styles of racing. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Auto Club's midget and three-quarter midget Western States Series 
program will headline the action, with a $15,000 purse up for grabs. 
</P>
<P>
Racing will begin at 7 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
A monster truck and four-wheel-drive pulling show will open the action tonight, 
with shows at 6 and 9. 
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, a field of 40 midget cars is expected to compete, with 1989 USAC 
Western States champion Robby Flock of the City of Industry among the entrants. 
</P>
<P>
Also, 40 three-quarter midgets are expected for a full program of races, 
including a 20-lap main event featuring current Western States points leader 
Jay Drake of Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Schroeder of Burbank, the winningest main-event driver in USAC 
three-quarter midget history, also will be in the field. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura's stock-car series, normally held on Friday nights, will move to a 6 
p.m. Sunday start to close the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
A contingent of about 25 street stocks and 25 mini stocks are scheduled to race 
in the one-quarter-mile dirt track oval and figure-eight races. 
</P>
<P>
More than 50 cars and drivers will compete for a $2,000 purse in the demolition 
derby immediately after the stock-car program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
