<P>
DRIFTER GETS 3 YEARS FOR PHONE BOX THEFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLUMBUS, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A drifter suspected of stealing up to $1 million from public telephone coin 
boxes in 32 states has been sentenced to three years in prison and ordered to 
repay Ohio Bell $802.50 in a plea bargain with authorities. 
</P>
<P>
Franklin County Judge Patrick McGrath sentenced James Clark to three 
consecutive one-year prison terms and to repay $802.50, little more than half 
of the more than $1,400 he is suspected of stealing from Columbus telephone 
booths. 
</P>
<P>
Clark pleaded guilty Wednesday to one count of theft and two counts of 
tampering with a coin machine. Ten other counts of tampering were dismissed in 
the plea bargain. 
