<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SCHLEVES AND READY MIX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I loved the letter from Leona Thomason (July 22) about Tom and Pat Schleve and 
Blue Star Ready Mix. 
</P>
<P>
It is about time someone spoke out against people who moved onto a street 
leading to a quarry and now are screaming their lungs out trying to get the 
quarry closed. It is my opinion that people who move next to quarries, 
airports, chicken ranches, freeways, dumps and other unaesthetic or unsavory 
places generally pay less for their property because of those very 
characteristics. To demand the closing of such establishments so that they may 
profit from increased land values at the expense of businesses and their 
employees is reprehensible and disgusting. 
</P>
<P>
EVELYN BURNS 
</P>
<P>
Camarillo 
</P>
</TEXT>
