<DATELINE>
<P>
BALTIMORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Safely Kept, the 1989 Eclipse Award winning sprinter, was established as an 8-5 
favorite Thursday for the first Frank J. DeFrancis Memorial Dash at Pimlico on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The Maryland-bred filly will start from the No. 5 post in the seven-horse field 
for $350,000 nationally-televised six furlong event. 
</P>
<P>
Second choice on the morning line is Sunny Blossom, a 5-year-old gelding who 
was shipped in from California for the race. He is listed at 5-2 and drew the 
sixth position. 
</P>
<P>
Others in the field include Sewickley, Glitterman, Brave Adventure, Kechi and 
Northern Wolf. 
