<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark Landsbaum and David Reyes 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ELVIS: The 13th anniversary of the king's death yesterday did not go 
unrecognized: There was a flurry of calls to the Nixon Library about Elvis 
Presley memorabilia. . . . Among the most popular items at the Yorba Linda 
facility is a chrome-plated .45-caliber pistol and six silver bullets Presley 
gave Nixon. . . . Most inquire about buying a copy of the photograph, above, 
taken on Dec. 21, 1970. Alas, copies are available only from the National 
Archives. The picture is the most requested photograph in the archives. 
