</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 28; Column 2; National Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
142 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN SHOOTS WIFE, TAKES SON HOSTAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man shot and wounded his wife and barricaded himself in his home with his 
3-year-old son Thursday, then surrendered to police after a brief volley of 
gunfire, a police official said. 
</P>
<P>
Mack Mulkey, 32, held his son in the three-story apartment building for four 
hours, police commander James Fruin said. 
</P>
<P>
Fruin said Mulkey, also known as John Polache, shot his common-law wife during 
a domestic dispute. 
</P>
<P>
Holly Potter, 29, was taken to Illinois Masonic Hospital with a wound to her 
left arm and was in good condition, Fruin said. Their son, Dillon Mulkey, was 
unharmed. 
</P>
<P>
The incident began about 4:45 a.m., police said. Mulkey fired several shots at 
police surrounding the apartment building before he surrendered about 9 a.m. No 
one was hit by the gunfire. 
</P>
<P>
Mulkey faces charges of aggravated burglary and aggravated assault, Fruin said. 
</P>
