<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-TITAN ABBOTT GIVEN TRYOUT WITH THE 49ERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROCKLIN, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former San Diego Chargers and Cal State Fullerton kicker Vince Abbott was given 
a tryout by the San Francisco 49ers on Thursday as the team continued to be 
concerned about the condition of kicker Mike Cofer. 
</P>
<P>
Cofer has been limited in his work by a pulled muscle in his left hip and is 
listed as probable for Monday night's game with Denver. 
</P>
<P>
"Looking at Abbott was just a precautionary measure," said John McVay, director 
of football operations. "We had former Minnesota kicker Chuck Nelson in 
Wednesday for a tryout and there is a possibility that we might sign one or the 
other." 
</P>
<P>
McVay said the team wouldn't have to make up its mind about signing a kicker 
until Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Cofer insisted he should be ready to play against the Broncos. 
</P>
<P>
"The muscle feels a lot better today than it has and I think I'll be able to 
kick," said Cofer, who missed Saturday night's game against the Raiders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ABBOTT, VINCE; FOOTBALL PLAYERS; SAN FRANCISCO 49ERS (FOOTBALL TEAM) 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA081790-0142 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 263311 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 17, 1990, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
View; Part E; Page 2; Column 2; View Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
