<TEXT>
<P>
North Carolina Is Tops for Manufacturers: Low wages, few unions and modest 
unemployment benefits give North Carolina the best manufacturing climate among 
the nation's industrial states, according to a study of business costs. 
California ranked 22nd among the 29 industrialized states, according to 
Chicago-based accounting firm Grant Thornton. Michigan had the worst 
manufacturing climate, with the highest average hourly wages, the highest 
percentage of union workers and high rankings in unemployment and workers' 
compensation benefits. 
</P>
