<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
SHORTAGES TO IDLE FORD PLANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ford Motor Co. said today it will idle its Mustang plant in Dearborn, Mich., 
for an additional week starting Monday, this time because of a shortage of 
engine parts. 
</P>
<P>
The plant, which employs 2,100 hourly workers who build about 3,700 Mustangs a 
week, was already idled this week because of a shortage of dealer orders. It 
will be closed next week because of a lack of four-cylinder engine parts, a 
company spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, Ford said it will idle car plants in Atlanta and Kansas 
City, Mo., the next week because of a shortage of dealer orders, affecting 
4,800 workers combined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
