<P>
NEW KIDS A HIGHWAY SENSATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NASHVILLE, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State and local law officers enlisted the aid of truck drivers to keep a swarm 
of motoring fans away from buses carrying the popular rock group New Kids on 
the Block. 
</P>
<P>
The truckers, called in on their citizens' band radios, formed a slow moving 
blockade on I-40 behind buses carrying the singers from a Thursday-night 
concert in Nashville to an appearance tonight in Knoxville. 
</P>
<P>
Police said that as many as 85 cars carrying fans had begun following the 
buses, often pulling their vehicles perilously close. 
</P>
<P>
"The bus drivers were having a little trouble with fans darting in and out in 
front of them trying to get a look inside the buses," said Roane County 
Sheriff's Deputy Dowell Isham. 
</P>
<P>
"They weren't trying to wreck the buses or anything. They were just trying to 
get a glimpse inside." 
</P>
</TEXT>
