<P>
ROONEY JR. LOOKING FOR A BREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mickey Rooney Jr. has endured a series of false career starts, but his 
autobiography -- "Which One's Your Mother?" -- and a couple of new country 
songs might signal the break he has been looking for. 
</P>
<P>
Rooney is still cautious even though his country songs "It Takes a Good Girl to 
Get Me" and "There's No Easy Way Out of This Love" have been greeted 
enthusiastically by record companies in Nashville. 
</P>
<P>
"The people there are very interested," he said Thursday, adding that he 
expected to sign a recording deal soon. But he is quick to temper his optimism, 
citing past experiences. 
</P>
<P>
"I've had eight record deals since I was a kid and it never went anywhere," he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Rooney is the first of the actor's 10 children. His mother is Betty Jane Baker. 
</P>
