<P>
COLLINS KNOCKS OUT CHIRINO -- BUT DON'T CALL HIM A PUNCHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Collins of Ireland doesn't want to get a reputation as a puncher because 
of his knockout victory over Furmin Chirino in a WBO middleweight match. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm punching harder, and tonight I proved I can punch when I have to," Collins 
said after Thursday's KO. "But I'm not going to be labeled a puncher. I'm still 
a boxer." 
</P>
<P>
Collins knocked out Chirino, who is from Venezuela, in the sixth round of the 
fight after pummeling him early on. 
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Collins lifted his record to 17-1 (with seven KOs) and earned 
the right to fight the winner of this Saturday's Iran Barkley-Nigel Benn match 
for the WBO middleweight title. 
</P>
