<P>
APPRENTICE RIDER HURT AT DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DEL MAR, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old apprentice jockey was injured when he was thrown by a horse 
during a workout at the Del Mar Race Track. 
</P>
<P>
Vann Belvoir incurred a minor back injury Thursday and was taken to Scripps 
Hospital in Encinitas, where he received 10 stitches to close cuts around his 
mouth, track spokesman Josh Rubinstein said. 
</P>
<P>
Belvoir, who is in his first season at the seaside track, will probably be out 
for three or four days, said his agent, Scotty McClellan. 
</P>
<P>
It was not known whether the horse, whose identity was not immediately 
available, would have to be destroyed. 
</P>
<P>
Belvoir was riding the horse in a simulated race when the animal broke its 
shoulder and fell. 
</P>
