</P>
<P>
* Amphibious dock landing ship Portland 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Additional Naval Forces 
</P>
<P>
The aircraft carrier John F. Kennedy is en route tot he coast of Saudi Arabia 
to either relieve the Eisenhower battle group or to perform additional tasks 
that may occur by ongoing events. The additional carrier will be the fourth 
added in the Persian Gulf. 
</P>
<P>
The Kennedy will carry about 80 aircraft including fighter planes, attack 
planes, radar aircraft, (including F-117A, Stealth fighters) as well as 
anti-submarine and search-and-rescue helicopters. 
</P>
<P>
The hospital ship Comfort, which beds 1,000 is also en route, while the Trenton 
and Portland are picking up troops en route to their deployment. 
</P>
